    <section id="postingbody">
        <div class="print-information print-qrcode-container">
            <p class="print-qrcode-label">QR Code Link to This Post</p>
            <div class="print-qrcode" data-location="https://norfolk.craigslist.org/apa/d/virginia-beach-short-term-rentals/7500681203.html"></div>
        </div>
Available from September 15 through March 15, there are two, 1-bedroom high-end, custom beach vacation rentals that are available for rent during the off-season. The properties are located at the Virginia Beach Oceanfront and are 5-blocks from the Boardwalk. Rent includes all utilities (water sewer, electric/hear/air, cable television and wifi), linens, and housewares. They are professionally decorated and fully furnished (all rental have sleeper sofas in addition to king size beds in bedrooms). The fully equipped kitchen feature full-size oven, full-size refrigerator with ice-maker, dishwasher, microwave oven, coffee maker, electric tea kettle, toaster and every item need for a comfortable stay. The rentals also include washer/dyer in every rental, ceiling fans, individually controlled central heating/cooling systems, 2 to 3 60-inch TV's, and there is driveway parking.  <br>
<br>
The property was constructed in 2012 and the rentals feature wood floors, custom wood work, wainscotting, crown molding, great lighting, custom tile work, large bathrooms, great closet space, individually controlled central heating/cooling systems, pantry, and breakfast serving bar.  There are two rental options are available and are as follows:<br>
<br>
                                    6-Month Lease (September 15 - March 15) $2,500 per month<br>
                                                                           or<br>
                                               Month-to-Month Lease  $3,000 per month<br>
<br>
The two rentals and are very similar.  Each has its own private entrance.  The property is also gated with extensive landscaping, private fenced yard, lots of outdoor decking with seating, outdoor recreational kitchen with running water and gas grill and an 8-person hot tub<br>
<br>
Where else can you live where the Virginia Beach Boardwalk is a short walk away, there are fireworks displays, parades, nightly concerts, and events like Something in the Water - The American Music Festival-Shamrock Marathon-East Coast Surfing Championships-Boardwalk Art Show as well as lots of great restaurants, night clubs and surfing?  This is only available at the coolest place to live in the region, The Virginia Beach Resort Area. <br>
<br>
Va Beach Oceanfront and 5-blocks to resort area.  Close enough to enjoy the area's boardwalk, restaurants, night clubs and all other activities provided in the resort area but yet far enough away from the noise.  3-blocks from I-264 and 10 minutes from Ft Story, NAS Oceana,  NAS Dam Neck, and Lynnhaven Mall.  Quiet residential neighborhood.   Located 20-minutes from downtown Norfolk and Norfolk Naval Bases.   <br>
<br>
 Comfortable, clean, and modern.  To see this property please call or text John  <a href="#" class="show-contact" title="click to show contact info" data-href="/reply/nfk/apa/7500681203/__SERVICE_ID__" rel="nofollow">show contact info</a>
 (owner/agent)<br>
